				<div class="postbody">
				I think Greenspan's idea of incorporating some sort of national sales tax and reducing the income tax is a good idea; kind of like a half-half type thing.
<br />

<br />
I would believe it would introduce less tax loopholes that the wealthy seem to be able to take advantage of because it would be tied directly to spending.  
<br />

<br />
I do feel that a tax based solely on a national sales tax would not be fair.  Yes wealthy people spend more but that spending is not necessarily linear when compared to the lower income people.  Many, if not all, wealthy people did not get that way by spending money like crazy.
<br />

<br />
What I find most interesting, though, is that there is at least a serious discussion about how to fix our revenue system.<br />
