			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				with sales tax, the poorest people have the biggest burden under it. A person that anualy spends 100% of their income to cover the costs of living, will have 100% of their income subjected to the sales tax. A person with more money, that say, spends only 50% of their income anualy, will only have 50% of their income subjected to the sales tax. The wealthier person will technicly pay more in sales tax in the year, but % is lower. IMO, sales tax ought to be done away with, aren't the republicans always trying to stimulate buisness growth? I know i'd buy more if I wasn't having to pay the 7.5% california sales tax on everything I buy. I'd spend exactly 7.5% more of my income.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
